default&#xa0;
defaultdo
default,
default particularly with the increase in the longer runs for h
defaultospital car journeys.
default&#xa0;
default6.1.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAn aging fleet of vehicles – a recent audit undertaken by NCTA identified that 70% of the bus fleet is between 5 – 10 years old and 27% is over 10 years old
default&#xa0;
default6.1.5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultChanges to D1 status of driving licences – this is a problem that is beginn
defaulting to occur as drivers who passed their tests after 
default1996
default n
defaulteed to take an additional test to be eligible to drive a minibus.  This costs over £1000 per driver and poses a significant extra cost for CTOs.  It also reinforces the dependency on older drivers 
defaultwho have D1 status on their licences
default.  
defaultCTO
defaults could attract younger drivers, pay for them to take the additional test to drive minibuses, only to lose them to commercial operators.  The CTO would then have to begin the recruitment process from scratch
default.
