defaultT
defaulthe time it takes the majority of passengers to get from their door onto the bus, to find their seat and put their seat belt on.  For individuals who travel in their wheelchair
defaults,
default 
defaultadditional time is required to apply all the safety restraints (6) for each wheelchair.  Those passengers who need a wheelchair or scooter to get from their house to the bus and 
defaultfrom the bus, 
defaultonce they have arrived 
defaultat their destination
default,
default take considerably l
defaultonger and therefore each journey is less time efficient than a similar journey undertaken by a commercial operator
