default6.2.
default 
defaultIn general, CTOs face the same issues as many other third sector organisations including an increasingly 
defaultcompetitive bidding process to win grant funding and the processes taking an increasing amount of time with more and more complexity in completing each application.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default7.1.
default 
defaultIn order to overcome these barriers, the following actions could be taken:
default&#xa0;
default7.1.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIncrease skills within CTOs to bid for and win contracts
default&#xa0;
default7.1.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPublic authorities take social value into account when issuing contracts, publish full details about when current 
defaultcontracts are due for renewal and bidding processes are advertised in good time.  Contracts are awarded on the basis of value for money over the lifetime of the contract rather than the lowest price
default&#xa0;
default7.1.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultContracts should be offered for 
defaultlonger periods, ideally 
defaulta 
defaultminimum 
defaultfive year term
default (with an option to extend a further 3 years)
default,
default which will 
defaultenable CTOs to plan over longer periods and become more sustainable businesses.
default&#xa0;
default7.1.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLocal support 
defaultshould
default 
defaultbe 
defaultavailable to assist in the recruitment of volunteers
default specifically for
default driving
default&#xa0;
default7.1.5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultInvestment funds are available to enable CTOs to buy new vehicles (Norfolk County Council is currently offering a Small Vehicles Fund of £250
default,000 but this is a one off oppo
defaultrtunity
default).  This should be conditional upon CTOs operating a depreciation p
defaultolicy with a vehicle replacement fund in their budgets.
default&#xa0;
default7.1.6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGovernment sh
defaultould review the D1 status on driving licenses or set up a ring fenced fund for CTOs to access funds for training drivers to drive minibuses.
default&#xa0;
default7.1.7.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGovernment should review the LTA Section
default19 s
defaultervice so that all CTOs are eligible to accept concessionary bus passes  without having to apply for and run a section 22 route.
